<subSubSection id="C31C656EFFC2190FFF6CFE5EFD32C0C2" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFC2190FFF6CFE5EFD32C0C2" blockId="11.[178,1085,429,481]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Etymology: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective) alludes to the conspicuously bisinuate posterior margin of the male sternite VIII.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C656EFFC2190FFF6CFE03FEC1C4F5" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFC2190FFF6CFE03FD23C37C" blockId="11.[178,1085,496,606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">
Description: Body length 
<quantity id="4CFE9B00FFC2190FFDFDFE03FDFAC327" box="[547,630,496,517]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.7" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162" unit="mm" value="9.7">9.7 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 5.0 mm. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFC2190FFF6CFDFEFF71C300" box="[178,253,525,547]" captionStart="Figs 18-27" captionStartId="12.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[181,1078,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 18-27: Pseudolathra armata nov.sp. (18-19) and P. bisinuata nov.sp. (20-27): (18, 23) male sternite VII; (19, 24) male sternite VIII; (20) habitus; (21) forebody; (22) antenna; (25-26) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (27) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 20-22: 1.0 mm; 18-19, 23-27: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307630/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
. Coloration: head dark-brown; pronotum and elytra reddish-brown, the latter with the posterior angles only very indistinctly and diffusely infuscate; abdomen brown with paler apex; legs dark-yellowish; antennae reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFC2190FFF6CFD9EFEE9C24F" blockId="11.[178,1086,621,877]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">
Head (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFC2190FFF29FD9EFECFC3A1" box="[247,323,621,643]" captionStart="Figs 18-27" captionStartId="12.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[181,1078,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 18-27: Pseudolathra armata nov.sp. (18-19) and P. bisinuata nov.sp. (20-27): (18, 23) male sternite VII; (19, 24) male sternite VIII; (20) habitus; (21) forebody; (22) antenna; (25-26) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (27) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 20-22: 1.0 mm; 18-19, 23-27: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307630/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) approximately as broad as long, of subquadrangular shape, with sharply marked posterior angles; lateral margins subparallel in dorsal view; punctation coarse, not umbilicate, rather dense in lateral and posterior dorsal portions, sparse in median and anterior dorsal portions, with interspersed micropunctation; interstices without microsculpture in median and anterior dorsal portions, with distinct microsculpture in lateral and in posterior dorsal portions. Eyes moderately large and moderately convex, but only little more than half as long as postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna slender, 
<quantity id="4CFE9B00FFC2190FFF3FFCC9FEBCC26D" box="[225,304,826,847]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
long; all antennomeres oblong; V-X of subequal length and with distinctly constricted bases.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFC2190FFF6CFC8EFEB8C2C8" blockId="11.[178,1085,892,1002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFC2190FFEFAFC8FFEE3C2B1" box="[292,367,892,915]" captionStart="Figs 18-27" captionStartId="12.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[181,1078,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 18-27: Pseudolathra armata nov.sp. (18-19) and P. bisinuata nov.sp. (20-27): (18, 23) male sternite VII; (19, 24) male sternite VIII; (20) habitus; (21) forebody; (22) antenna; (25-26) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (27) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 20-22: 1.0 mm; 18-19, 23-27: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307630/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) 1.05 times as long as broad and nearly as broad as head; lateral margins very weakly converging posteriad; punctation similar to that of head, but less dense and without distinct micropunctation; separate dorsal series absent; impunctate midline rather broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFC2190FFF6CFC09FC6FC568" blockId="11.[178,1085,1018,1098]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFC2190FFF21FC09FEC5C532" box="[255,329,1018,1040]" captionStart="Figs 18-27" captionStartId="12.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[181,1078,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 18-27: Pseudolathra armata nov.sp. (18-19) and P. bisinuata nov.sp. (20-27): (18, 23) male sternite VII; (19, 24) male sternite VIII; (20) habitus; (21) forebody; (22) antenna; (25-26) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (27) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 20-22: 1.0 mm; 18-19, 23-27: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307630/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) 1.07 times as long as pronotum; punctation shallow, arranged in longitudinal series. Hind wings fully developed. Legs rather short; metatarsomere I short and weakly oblong, approximately as long as II; protarsomeres I-IV strongly dilated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFC2190FFF6CFBAAFD8CC5E5" blockId="11.[178,1085,1113,1223]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Abdomen slender, approximately 0.8 times as broad as elytra; punctation fine, moderately dense on tergites III-VI, somewhat sparser and finer on tergite VII, very sparse on tergite VIII; interstices with distinct microreticulation; posterior margin of tergite VII with pronounced palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFC2190FFF19FB24FEC1C4F5" blockId="11.[178,1086,1238,1495]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">
: postero-lateral processes of tergite IX (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFC2190FFDA3FB25FD47C5CF" box="[637,715,1238,1261]" captionStart="Figs 28-30" captionStartId="13.[178,218,784,806]" captionTargetBox="[178,1082,218,754]" captionTargetId="figure-1@13.[178,1082,212,767]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 28-30: Pseudolathra armata nov.sp. (28) and P. bisinuata nov.sp. (29-30): (28-29) anteromedian portion of male sternite VII; (30) male segments IX-X. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307632/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
) strongly asymmetric, left process (dorsal view) much longer than right process; sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFC2190FFCBEFB07FC38C428" box="[864,948,1268,1290]" captionStart="Figs 18-27" captionStartId="12.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[181,1078,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 18-27: Pseudolathra armata nov.sp. (18-19) and P. bisinuata nov.sp. (20-27): (18, 23) male sternite VII; (19, 24) male sternite VIII; (20) habitus; (21) forebody; (22) antenna; (25-26) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (27) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 20-22: 1.0 mm; 18-19, 23-27: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307630/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) moderately transverse, posterior margin weakly concave, pubescence sparse, near middle of anterior margin with a cluster of gland openings; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFC2190FFCC8FADDFCEBC466" box="[790,871,1326,1348]" captionStart="Figs 18-27" captionStartId="12.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[181,1078,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 18-27: Pseudolathra armata nov.sp. (18-19) and P. bisinuata nov.sp. (20-27): (18, 23) male sternite VII; (19, 24) male sternite VIII; (20) habitus; (21) forebody; (22) antenna; (25-26) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (27) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 20-22: 1.0 mm; 18-19, 23-27: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307630/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) weakly transverse, posteriorly produced, posterior excision broad and very shallow, thus rendering the posterior margin bisinuate; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFC2190FFD9BFA9AFD35C45D" box="[581,697,1385,1407]" captionStart="Figs 18-27" captionStartId="12.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[181,1078,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@12.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 18-27: Pseudolathra armata nov.sp. (18-19) and P. bisinuata nov.sp. (20-27): (18, 23) male sternite VII; (19, 24) male sternite VIII; (20) habitus; (21) forebody; (22) antenna; (25-26) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (27) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 20-22: 1.0 mm; 18-19, 23-27: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307630" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307630/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1162">Figs 25-27</figureCitation>
) approximately 
