<subSubSection id="C31C656EFFC7190AFF6CFF28FC14C06B" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFC7190AFF6CFF28FC14C06B" blockId="14.[178,1085,219,329]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165">
Comparative notes: Like the preceding species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D66FFC7190AFC8EFF28FC5DC1D2" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2014" box="[848,977,219,240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisinuata">
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFC7190AFC8EFF28FC5DC1D2" box="[848,977,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165">P. bisinuata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
evidently belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D66FFC7190AFE90FF0AFE51C02F" baseAuthorityName="Cameron" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[334,477,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriceps">
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFC7190AFE90FF0AFE51C02F" box="[334,477,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165">P. quadriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. It differs from the other species of this group particularly by the morphology of the male tergite IX, the conspicuously shaped posterior margin of the male sternite VIII, and by the morphology of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C656EFFC7190AFF6CFEABFDFBC08A" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFC7190AFF6CFEABFDFBC08A" blockId="14.[178,1085,344,424]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165">
Distribution and natural history: The type locality is situated somewhere in the Kinabatangan river valley in 
<collectingRegion id="49C2F807FFC7190AFD47FE86FD55C0A9" box="[665,729,373,395]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165">Sabah</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3117675FFC7190AFD3BFE86FCF8C0A9" box="[741,884,373,395]" name="Malaysia" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165">North Borneo</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3117675FFC7190AFCA1FE86FC50C0A9" box="[895,988,373,395]" name="Malaysia" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFC7190AFC34FE86FBBDC0A9" box="[1002,1073,373,395]" captionStart="Map 2" captionStartId="13.[178,223,1482,1503]" captionTargetBox="[178,1083,859,1464]" captionTargetId="figure-38@13.[178,1083,859,1464]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Map 2: Distributions of Pseudolathra armata (black triangles), P. bisinuata (star), P. sepikensis (white circle), P. naviculum (black circle), P. puncta (white triangle), and P. cyanea (diamond)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307636/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165">Map 2</figureCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="54BD8847FFC7190AFF3EFE61FEB5C08A" box="[224,313,402,424]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1165">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected at a light source.
</paragraph>
